        <updateDate>2021-04-08T22:17:26Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Blackwater Trading Post Land Transfer Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of the Interior to take the approximately 55.3 acres of land of the Blackwater Trading Post in Pinal County, Arizona, into trust for the benefit of the Gila River Indian Community, if the community conveys to Interior all of its interest in the land. The land is made part of the community's reservation. </p> <p>Further, the bill prohibits gaming on the land taken into trust.</p>]]>
        </text>
